<br>
Won't always work out, but sometimes it works out really well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#778899>(9/28/01 4:01:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Plane Raids Question</span><hr size=1> To address both issues you raised --<br>
<br>
If the epic drops weren't in the planes, there would be a LOT fewer people attending them, and almost all the strife would disappear.<br>
<br>
The armor that drops is not as nice as what drops in Kunark or Velious.  Guilds capable of success in the planes are capable of success in these other areas.<br>
<br>
However, a lot of the people who do go regard planar gear as upgrades to what they currently have.  It's a stepping stone to uberness, so to speak.<br>
<br>
Others of us go to support our friends and because we want the epic drops.<br>
<br>
Personally, I want 2 things from the planes -- the drop off the Shissar in Fear (chanter epic), and the chanter halo from Hate.  However, the Thurgadin halo is probably better, and my time would be far better served if I spent it in the Kael arena area.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Guests on Raids</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> -- horizons raids are usually semi-open signup.  Roughly half the raid will be non-Horizons members.  Note that we dual-book with one or two other guilds, but we still take other guests.<br>
<br>
Everyone has equal looting rights for planar gear, regardless of guild affiliation.  Special rules for robes/breastplates, but the rule is related to having been with us on previous raids and again is unrelated to guild affiliation.<br>
<br>
Epic drops are usually pre-arranged, although there are always epic drops available that are /random within class the day of the raid.  When we pre-arrange, it's usually again with note towards people who have attended our previous raids.<br>
<br>
For instance, on our last Fear raid, Zwobu from Trade Foundation did his wizzie epic thing with the broken golem.<br>
<br>
Sharyls advice is sound.  Watch the calendar.  Note that you can click on the individual events to find that some of them (like Horizons) will tell you how to contact us if you wanted to go along.<br>
